<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,325,629]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,495,521]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male antennae without spines in antennomeres V or VI; lateral tubercles of the prothorax acute, coincident or not with posterolateral angles; pro- and mesoventral processes less than one-fourth of the width of the procoxal cavity; elytra without centrobasal crest or carinae. Number of species currently included: 78; in 
<collectingCountry box="[1351,1437,567,593]" name="Mexico" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Central 
<taxonomicName box="[286,387,603,629]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">America</taxonomicName>
: 19.
</paragraph>
